{"author":"The Ecclesiastical History, Dialogues, and Letters of Theodoret","book":"The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","chapter":155,"classification":{"bucket":"Patristic / broadly orthodox","canonicalStatus":"patristic","contentKind":"primary","cautionReason":"No major mainstream heresy warning is attached by the preview classifier.","doctrinalStatus":"orthodox","labels":["patristic"],"severity":0},"id":"npnf203:iv.viii.v.xxxix","lineage":["The Ecclesiastical History, Dialogues, and Letters of Theodoret.","The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","Book V","Of Theodorus, bishop of Mopsuestia."],"metadata":{"author":"The Ecclesiastical History, Dialogues, and Letters of Theodoret","authorshipDateRange":null,"ccel":{"id":"npnf203","sourceUrl":"https://www.ccel.org/ccel/schaff/npnf203.xml","title":"NPNF2-03. Theodoret, Jerome, Gennadius, & Rufinus: Historical Writings"},"source":{"id":"npnf203","provider":"CCEL","sourceUrl":"https://www.ccel.org/ccel/schaff/npnf203.xml","title":"NPNF2-03. Theodoret, Jerome, Gennadius, & Rufinus: Historical Writings"}},"originalBook":"Book V","sourceVolumeId":"npnf203","title":"Of Theodorus, bishop of Mopsuestia.","source":{"id":"npnf203","sourceUrl":"https://www.ccel.org/ccel/schaff/npnf203.xml","title":"NPNF2-03. Theodoret, Jerome, Gennadius, & Rufinus: Historical Writings"},"verses":[{"book":"The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","chapter":155,"text":"When the divine Theodorus was ruling the church of Antioch, Theodorus, bishop of Mopsuestia, a doctor of the whole church and successful combatant against every heretical phalanx, ended this life.","verse":1},{"book":"The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","chapter":155,"text":"He had enjoyed the teaching of the great Diodorus, and was the friend and fellow-worker of the holy John, for they both together benefited by the spiritual draughts given by Diodorus.","verse":2},{"book":"The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","chapter":155,"text":"Six-and-thirty years he had spent in his bishopric, fighting against the forces of Arius and Eunomius, struggling against the piratical band of Apollinarius, and finding the best pasture for God’s sheep.","verse":3},{"book":"The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","chapter":155,"text":"His brother Polychronius was the excellent bishop of Apamea, a man gifted with great eloquence and of illustrious character.","verse":4},{"book":"The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","chapter":155,"text":"I shall now make an end of my history, and shall entreat those who meet with it to requite my labour with their prayers.","verse":5},{"book":"The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","chapter":155,"text":"The narrative now embraces a period of 105 years, beginning from the Arian madness and ending with the death of the admirable Theodorus and Theodotus.","verse":6},{"book":"The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","chapter":155,"text":"I will give a list of the bishops of great cities after the persecution.","verse":7},{"book":"The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","chapter":155,"text":"List of the bishops of great cities.","verse":8},{"book":"The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","chapter":155,"text":"Miltiades.............................................................................................","verse":9},{"book":"The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","chapter":155,"text":"[Melchiades.","verse":10},{"book":"The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","chapter":155,"text":"Silvester..................................................................................................................","verse":11},{"book":"The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","chapter":155,"text":"Julius................................................................................","verse":12},{"book":"The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","chapter":155,"text":"Mark Jan. to Oct., 336]","verse":13},{"book":"The Ecclesiastical History of Theodoret.","chapter":155,"text":"Liberius.....................